-- Syria’s Shara Wants Talks Without Preconditions, Watan Reports
-- B y   D o n n a   A b u - N a s r
-- 2012-08-28T08:46:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-28/syria-s-shara-wants-talks-without-preconditions-watan-reports.html
Syria’s Vice President Faruq al- Shara said that an end to violence and national dialogue without
preconditions are the basis for a settlement to the Syrian
crisis, the pro-government  Al Watan  newspaper said.  Al-Shara’s remarks came during an Aug. 26 meeting with the
chairman of  Iran ’s Security and Foreign Policy Commission,
 Alaeddin Boroujerdi , Al-Shara’s unidentified assistant told the
newspaper. The government of President Bashar al-Assad earlier
denied a report by the Dubai-based Al Arabiya channel that Shara
had defected.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Donna Abu-Nasr in Beirut at 
 dabunasr@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  